The Presidential Candidate of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA), Prof. Peter Umeadi has urged Igbo traditional rulers in the 19 northern states to work hard in conjunction with his running mate, Alhaji Abdullahi Koli Mohammed, to win the northern votes for the party to clinch the presidential seat in the 2023 general election. Umeadi who eulogised his running mate, Mohammed, said APGA is a great project because of the quality of the personalities flying the party’s flag. The presidential candidate who was a Chief Judge of Anambra State, spoke in Abuja when the Association of Ndieze Igbo in the 19 northern states endorsed his candidature. He said, “You now have a capable man who will assist you every inch of the way in the north in a bid to delivering APGA in the north. The party now has a national outlook and a credible and formidable team which we will take to the 2023 elections where we hope to emerge victorious.”